id: AIC-COMPILE-001
type: module
owner: business
extends: project.intent

module: aic compile
command: aic compile <ComponentName> --target <language@version>
description: >
  Compiles a component.intent file to a target language and version
  using the configured AI provider. Uses delta-based compilation —
  reads existing generated file and updates only what changed.
  Never fully regenerates unless --force flag is passed.
  Writes a lockfile on completion.

behaviors:
  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-B1
    intent: |
      Validate the project is initialised and git is present.
      Validate component name exists in the target language folder.
      Validate target language and optional version are supported.
      Validate AI provider is configured in aic.config.json.
      Fail loudly on any validation failure before touching any file.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-B2
    intent: |
      Phase 1 — Retrieval (fully deterministic, zero LLM).
      Read component.intent for the specified component and language.
      Resolve full inheritance chain in order:
        1. project.intent
        2. language.intent for target language
        3. business/<ComponentName>/module.intent
        4. <language>/<ComponentName>/ComponentName.intent
      Load all referenced standards files declared in project.intent.
      Read existing generated code file if it exists.
      Read lockfile if it exists.
      All steps are pure file I/O — no AI involved.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-B3
    intent: |
      Phase 2 — Diff (fully deterministic, zero LLM).
      Compare current intent hash against lockfile snapshot.
      Identify exactly which sections of intent changed.
      If no lockfile exists treat entire intent as new — full generation.
      If lockfile exists produce a precise delta:
        - Which behavior IDs changed
        - Which implementation details changed
        - Which overrides changed
      Pass only the delta to Phase 3 — not the full intent.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-B4
    intent: |
      Phase 3 — Inference (LLM).
      Build a structured prompt containing:
        - Full project standards context
        - Language guidelines context
        - Business intent context
        - Component intent delta only
        - Existing generated code if present
        - Target language and version
      Send to configured AI provider.
      Receive generated or updated code back.
      This is the only phase where AI is involved.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-B5
    intent: |
      Phase 4 — Validation and write (deterministic).
      Write generated code to the output file.
      Compute new intent hash.
      Write updated lockfile recording:
        - intent hash
        - provider and model used
        - target language and version
        - timestamp
      Never write the lockfile if code generation failed.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-B6
    intent: |
      Support --force flag to bypass delta and fully regenerate.
      Useful when generated file is corrupted or needs clean slate.
      --force deletes existing lockfile before compiling.
      Warn developer that full regeneration is happening.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-B7
    intent: |
      Support --verify flag to run static validation after generation.
      Check generated output declares all behaviors from intent.
      Log verification result in lockfile.
      Warn but do not fail if verification finds gaps —
      developer makes final call.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-B8
    intent: |
      Print clear progress output for each phase.
      Phase 1: show which files were read
      Phase 2: show what changed in delta
      Phase 3: show which provider was called
      Phase 4: show what was written
      Total time taken printed at end.

journeys:
  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Runs aic compile UserService --target python
    outcome: |
      Inheritance chain resolved.
      Delta computed against lockfile.
      AI updates only changed sections.
      user_service.py updated surgically.
      Lockfile updated.
      Git diff is clean and minimal.

  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Runs aic compile UserService --target python
      for the first time — no lockfile exists
    outcome: |
      Full generation from intent.
      user_service.py created fresh.
      Lockfile created with initial snapshot.

  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Runs aic compile UserService --target python --force
    outcome: |
      Warning printed — full regeneration happening.
      Existing lockfile deleted.
      Full generation from intent.
      New lockfile created.

  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Runs aic compile UserService --target java@21
    outcome: |
      Same intent file compiled to Java 21.
      Version passed as context to AI.
      Java 21 idiomatic code generated.
      Separate lockfile for java@21 target.

failure-modes:
  - scenario: AIC not initialised
    response: Exit code 1 — suggest aic init

  - scenario: Component not found
    response: Exit code 1 — suggest aic create

  - scenario: AI provider not configured
    response: Exit code 1 — suggest filling aic.config.json

  - scenario: AI provider call fails
    response: Exit code 2 — show provider error, no files written

  - scenario: Output file write fails
    response: Exit code 2 — show path, lockfile not written

  - scenario: Intent file malformed
    response: Exit code 1 — show which file and what is wrong